                             HOW TO PARTICIPATE


                                                     NASA will collaborate
                                              on research with outstanding
                                         educational institutions, as well
                                             as cutting-edge companies and
                                                  non-profit organizations
                                                     at NASA Research Park

   [HeadContours.jpg] Key Partnership Areas
    Astrobiology
    Biotech
    High-Performance Computing
    High-Speed Networking
    Human Factors
    Information Technology
    Intelligent Systems
    Microgravity Research
    Nanotechnology
    New Materials & Thermal Systems

   [ParticipateOpener.jpg]

   They will come from the integration of these segments, each making the
   most of its unique attributes--NASA's focus on high-risk, long-term
   research; industry's abilitiy to react quickly with applied

   technologies; and academia's expertise in educating and training a
   vibrant work force for the future. At the NASA Research Park, Ames
   Research Center partners provide educational opportunities consistent
   with NASA's mission.

     Partners must meet the following criteria:

      Support NASA's mission under the Space Act (42 U.S.C. õ2451 set
     seq.)
      Comply with site environmental constraints and community
     partnership agreements
