                         About Ames Research Center


        Ames is one of ten NASA centers throughout the United States
    It is located in the heart of the Silicon Valley at Moffett Field in
                                 California

                        Ames Leads Key NASA Research


                    picture of virtual air control tower

     Aerospace Operations Systems research at Ames has a long history of
    improving air traffic control and aircraft performance.  The program
    aims to make major reductions in aircraft accidents and to triple the
                      national airspace system by 2010.
                                space collage

        Astrobiology is the study of Earth science, space science and
     evolutionary biology. Ames researchers seek answers to fundamental
   questions about the origin of life, the existence of life beyond Earth
                and the future of life on Earth and in space.
                         high-tech image of a human

       Information Technology research at Ames is infusing innovative
   approaches and technologies into all of NASA's programs, including the
        Space Shuttle and the Space Station. Researchers also work on
     intelligent systems to explore the universe, computer models of the
   Earth to help us understand its complex workings and new ways to handle
                         increasing amounts of data.

